issues.description: The problem statement and template specify an interface named `Milkable`, but the solution repository defines the interface as `Dairy` and never provides a `Milkable` interface. Moreover, `Main.java` in the solution still refers to `Milkable`, which does not exist. This naming mismatch will confuse students and prevent the solution code from compiling as specified.
issues.suggested_fix: Rename the `Dairy` interface in the solution to `Milkable` (including the filename and all references), and ensure that both the interface and its usages match the problem specification.

issues.description: The interface for milking is called “Milkable” in the problem statement and referenced in the template’s Main.java, but in the solution repository it is named “Dairy”, causing a mismatch in the conceptual mapping of the milking capability.
issues.suggested_fix: Rename the solution’s Dairy interface to Milkable (and update Seal and Goat to implement Milkable) so that the interface name matches the problem statement and template.
